The condition of the finish is a bit worn and has some freckling and a spot where the nickel is worn by the trigger guard. Generally a refinished gun has the engraving filled a bit. I have a refinished 1903 in blue that someone had done, the engraving is softened because of the blueing filling the roll engraving. Not the case with this gun.
